genresAdvancedInfo.name: guqin
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A traditional Chinese music genre that is played on a seven-stringed instrument of the same name. The music is characterized by its slow, meditative pace and delicate, intricate melodies. Guqin music is often associated with scholarly pursuits and is known for its ability to evoke a sense of calm and tranquility.
